 glutamate to glutamate-gamma-semialdehyde is speculative and likely the bottleneck. The final reduction of P5C to proline is plausible but not specifically demonstrated prebiotically for this system. Overall, pathway logic is good but key connector steps remain under-supported.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_004\",\n        \"rxn_005\",\n        \"rxn_007\",\n        \"rxn_009\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Specify mineral/reductant support for glutamate-to-semialdehyde reduction, ideally FeS/Ni or pyrite-linked conditions from the literature context.\",\n        \"Downgrade alpha-ketoglutarate synthesis to speculative unless a documented protometabolic route is cited.\",\n        \"Clarify whether the final proline is racemic rather than L-specific, since no chiral induction is provided.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.55,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.38,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.86,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.42,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.58\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.61,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.74,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.78,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.82,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.69,\n      \"feedback\": \"The pathway is chemically connected but relies heavily on a glycolaldehyde-assisted route to alpha-ketoglutarate that is only weakly grounded in the provided literature. Glycolaldehyde is a useful carbonyl hub, but using it to reach alpha-ketoglutarate in vent chemistry is speculative. Downstream glutamate/P5C/proline logic remains reasonable. This route is less literature-secure than the canonical alpha-ketoglutarate-centered route.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_004\",\n        \"rxn_005\",\n        \"rxn_007\",\n       