ment that experimental support for this route is limited.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.55,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.2,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.2,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.1\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.26,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.3,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.39,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.25,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.27,\n      \"feedback\": \"This formamide-assisted UV-radical route is weakly supported. While formamide is a relevant prebiotic intermediate, the specific sequence to butylamine and then to proline is not established by the cited literature in the surface environment used here. The branch appears to infer too much from limited astrochemical observations.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_009\",\n        \"rxn_010\",\n        \"rxn_012\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Constrain this route to ice photochemistry conditions if retained.\",\n        \"Substitute more defensible mixed-product UV chemistry rather than a linear butylamine route.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.2,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.2,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.05\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.15,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.22,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.21,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.18,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.18,\n      \"feedback\": \"This is the weakest pathway. Meteorite delivery is not a reaction from water to proline, and the butylamine-centered steps lack sufficient experimental grounding in the encoded environment. The pathway is not chemically constructed in a defensible network sense.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_009\",\n        \"rxn_010\",\n        \"rxn_011\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Model meteoritic input as an exogenous source node or transfer process, not as H2O to proline chemistry.\",\n        \"Remove or heavily qualify the butylamine route.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.05,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.1\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.08,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.18,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.12,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.15,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.11,\n      \"feedback\": \"Meteoritic delivery is relevant to proline availability, but it is not represented as a chemically valid reaction here. Water cannot be treated as the reactant yielding proline. The final L-proline integration step is likewise not a synthesis reaction. This pathway should be represented as environmental import, not chemistry.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_011\",\n        \"rxn_012\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Represent meteoritic delivery as a source term or transfer edge rather than a reaction node.\",\n        \"Separate environmental accumulation from chemical synthesis.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n  \"overall_confidence\": 0.42,\n  \"network_feedback\": \"The network has decent high-level topology and correctly recognizes the literature reality that dedicated prebiotic L-proline synthesis is unproven. It includes multiple convergent branches toward a shared proline pool and identifies sensible hub molecules such as HCN, alpha-ketoglutarate, glutamate, P5C, and proline. However, the network falls below approval due to substantial chemical and representational weaknesses. The strongest literature-supported chemistry is direct mixed-product proline formation in spark-discharge experiments and exogenous meteoritic delivery, but the network weakens itself by encoding speculative or non-reaction steps as if they were validated synthesis reactions